<text xml:lang="ta">
  <body>
    <div xml:id="PN287-intro">
      <p type="edition">tiṇai – karantai; tuṟai – nīṇmoḻi. cāttantaiyār.
      </p>
      <p xml:lang="en" type="translation">  
      </p>
    </div>  
    <div xml:id="PN287">
      <lg type="edition">
<l>tuṭiyeṟiyum pulaiya</l>
<l>veṟikōl koḷḷu miḻiciṉa</l>
<l>kāla māriyi ṉampu taippiṉum</l>
<l>vayaṟkeṇṭaiyiṉ vēlpiṟaḻiṉum</l>
<l>polampuṉai yōṭai yaṇṇal yāṉai</l>
<l>yilaṅkuvāṉ maruppi ṉutimaṭut tūṉṟiṉu</l>
<l>mōṭal cellāp pīṭuṭai yāḷar</l>
<l>neṭunīrp poykaip piṟaḻiya vāḷai</l>
<l>nelluṭai neṭunakark kūṭṭumutaṟ puraḷun</l>
<l>taṇṇaṭai peṟutal yāvatu paṭiṉē</l>
<l>māciṉ makaḷir maṉṟa ṉaṉṟu</l>
<l>muyarnilai yulakattu nukarpa vataṉāl</l>
<l>vampa vēntaṉ ṟāṉai</l>
<l>yimpar niṉṟum kāṇṭirō varavē.</l>
</lg>
<lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>Drummer who beats the Tuṭi drum,</l>
<l>lowcaste man(?) who takes the fighting stick,</l>
<l>Great men who don’t go running,</l>
<l>although pierced with arrows as with timely showers,</l>
<l>although spears leap [at them] like Keṇṭai fish in the tank,</l>
<l>although the tips of the shining pure tusks of majestic elephants </l>
<l>with gold-decorated front-plates gore [and] fix [onto them],</l>
<l>what of [their] obtaining a villages,</l>
<l>that abound in granaries in large mansions that possess paddy</l>
<l>[and] Vāḷai fish that leap in the ponds with long water?</l>
<l>	If they fall,</l>
<l>they will enjoy well the marriage with faultless women</l>
<l>in the world of high standing. Therefore,</l>
<l>although standing here, would you see the coming </l>
<l>of the new king’s army?</l>
</lg>
    </div>
